node.text:
Coached by @Crystalrose.Sanders, these skaters aged 8-20 and leveled from preliminary to senior, show that skating is all about perseverance and hard work, no matter how hard things may get. Keep your head up, stay motivated and don't let anyone stop you from your goals and dreams.

Good luck to all the skaters at National Showcase this week!!!

🎥 by Jordan @oniceperspectives

@icegirlash and Timothy LeDuc’s 2021-22 Senior Pairs Short Program is now available on On Ice Perspectives’ YouTube channel. It was meant to premiere with their debut performance this weekend at Cranberry Cup. Unfortunately, in the week between filming this and leaving for competition, Ashley was exposed to COVID-19, and despite being a world class athlete, fully-vaccinated, and wearing masks with her students, she was still affected enough to require hospitalization and miss their first competition since Worlds. The good news is that Ash is already doing better, testing negative again and will soon be out of quarantine and back to preparing for her and Tim’s next competition.

It’s important for us all to remember that COVID-19 is still a serious and deadly disease, not just for the unvaccinated, or immunocompromised, but also for the people in our lives we’d least expect. To protect them and get to the end of this pandemic, we need to stay vigilant with masks in crowded spaces, follow social distancing guidelines, and most importantly, get you and your loved ones vaccinated to protect against the worst side effects and reduce the spread of variants. I myself choose all three, and am grateful for the opportunity, and privilege, to travel and film and bring skating to everyone who cannot experience it in person right now. Stay safe, on and off the ice. - Jordan @oniceperspectives

__⛸ Ashley Cain-Gribble & Timothy LeDuc
__🎥 by Jordan @oniceperspectives
__🎵 “Nureyev” from ‘The White Crow’ by @LisaBatiashvili  @Dudana_Mazmani

Three years ago today I made my first trip to the @iceacademyofmontreal, and the first video I posted was @oliviasmartx and @adriandiazbronchud training the Tango Romantica, the 2018-19 season’s Pattern Dance… So it’s only fitting that on my first trip back to Montreal this year, I get to share this clip of Olivia and Adrian training this season’s Pattern Dance, the Midnight Blues! The theme for Rhythm Dance this year is “Street Dance”, with official rulebook examples ranging from blues to reggae, jazz to funk, and even hip-pop, popping and krump. Suffice to say it’s going to be a very entertaining Olympic Ice Dance season!

__⛸ @oliviasmartx & @adriandiazbronchud (🇪🇸 Spain) 2021-22 Rhythm Dance 
__🎵 Proud Mary @tinaturner
__🎥 by Jordan @oniceperspectives

Even falls can be choreo when you’re improvising on ice! ⛸ @kjerstynhall @choreobyk + @americanicetheatre.

Have you ever tried improvising dance moves on ice with your friends? I get to see a lot of figure skaters cross over to floor dance and vice versa, but rarely do skaters get to improv on a freestyle session unless it’s totally empty. @americanicetheatre bridges that gap between contemporary dancing and figure skating, and I’m proud to have worked with their skaters for many years, since I first started filming on the ice. Check out my YouTube page for this video in its entirety, and you’ll also see a link to a working playlist containing all of the 2021 American Contemporary Skating Festival performances (updated as I upload them)!
